high priority:
    [x] native integer-power operator: IntPow(x, n) for n ∈ {2,3,4,5,6} instead of continuous Power(p) — avoids fractional p drift on high-degree polys
    [x] proper division node: explicit x/y node added; soft Arithmetic remains for backward compatibility
    [x] multi-start: run 3-5 independent evolutions and pick best — matches PySR's multi-run protocol
    [x] adaptive compute budget: easy formulas get short budgets, hard formulas get expanded budgets (configurable min/max)
